SIMPLE: sluggish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sluggish
<hw>Slug"gish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Habitually idle and lazy; slothful; dull; inactive; <as>as, a
<ex>sluggish</ex> man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Slow; having little motion; <as>as, a
<ex>sluggish</ex> stream</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having no power to move one's self or itself;
inert.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Matter, being impotent, <qex>sluggish</qex>, and inactive, hath no
power to stir or move itself.</q> <rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the <qex>sluggish</qex> land slumbers in utter neglect.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Characteristic of a sluggard; dull; stupid; tame;
simple.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧So <xex>sluggish</xex> a
conceit.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Inert; idle; lazy; slothful; indolent; dronish;
slow; dull; drowsy; inactive. See <er>Inert</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Slug"gish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Slug"gish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sluggy</ent>⟦br⟧
